data.name: radioButton5.ToolTip
data.value: The flow field around buildings is computed with an internal simple prognostic wind field model and a k-l turbulence model. Slower than the diagnostic approach but usually better results. Useful for small and medium model domains (<~6x6 km²).

data.name: radioButton4.ToolTip
data.value: Simple diagnostic wind field calculation - not recommended! The flow field is set to zero inside buildings. Mass conservation in the flow field is achieved with a very simple approach. Fast, high uncertainty in the computed concentrations. Useful for very large model domains (>~6x6 km²).

data.name: checkBox26.ToolTip
data.value:
GRAL writes the calculated flow fields to *.gff files. This saves simulation time in the transient GRAL mode or if more than one dispersion simulation is performed without changing building geometries, or any other item influencing the flow field compuations.
!!Caution: May require extremely large disk space!!
